"""
Itinerary HTML Validator (static checks ‚Äî no network).

Enforces hygiene and format rules from `Travel/CLAUDE.md` (the operational
spine) plus the locked content rules in `Brain/CORE RULES/*.html`. Structural
contract for the HTML lives in comments in `Brain/Reference/Guide Style.css`.

‚öÝÔ∏è  STANDING ORDER ‚Äî VALIDATOR CHECK BEFORE GUIDE FIX (2026-05-08, Dani)
    When ANY violation is found in a guide:
      1. Write the check here first ‚Äî fire on bad, pass on clean.
      2. Run the validator ‚Üí guide fails.
      3. Fix the guide to make it pass.
    NEVER fix the guide first. A guide fix without a check is a one-time
    repair. The check is the permanent fix for every future guide.
    Documented failure: abbreviated weekday names (Mon/Tue etc.) in üèõ rows ‚Äî
    rule changed, check not written ‚Üí 50 violations across 6 audited guides.

Rule source: `Brain/CORE RULES/*.html` ‚Äî one file per topic. See
`Brain/Reference/Separation Map.md` for the canonical topic-to-file mapping.
All rule-comment references use the current CORE RULES file names.

Companion scripts for the full pre-ship verification:
  - ./verify_urls.py     ‚Äî fetches every href and img src, reports
                           status codes, flags city-landing redirects.
  - ./commons_photo.py   ‚Äî resolves Wikimedia Commons filenames to
                           canonical 800px thumb URLs via the Commons API.

Full pre-ship pipeline:
  python3 validate_itinerary.py <guide.html>  &&  python3 verify_urls.py <guide.html>

Usage: python3 validate_itinerary.py <file.html>
"""

