    ("2026-06-16", "DAY TRIPS ‚Äî Omio booking link text must be exactly 'Omio' (Dani 2026-06-16, Berlin: mixed 'Omio'/'omio'/'omio.com'). CORE RULES edited: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß2 template '[omio]' ‚Üí 'Omio', coverage-exception paragraph now states the entry is written exactly as 'Omio' in title case (checksums regenerated, doc_workshop_validator clean). New check: every <a> in the Day Trips section whose href contains 'omio' must have anchor text exactly 'Omio'. Scoped to Omio-covered regions (China-exempt). EXPECTED to fail: many guides incl. Berlin, Zurich (omio.com)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "GETTING AROUND üö¢ FERRY ‚Äî negative-finding line is now DRIFT (Dani 2026-06-16: 'remove that from the rules ‚Ä¶ this was a drift'). CORE RULES edited: Getting Around - Extra Section.html ¬ß4 removed 'If no ferry is relevant, ship No ferry available in [City].'; the Ferry subsection is now omitted entirely when no relevant ferry route exists (checksums regenerated, doc_workshop_validator clean). New check: a üö¢ Ferry extras-sub followed by a ferry negative-finding line ('No ferry available', 'does not have a ferry', 'no ferry') hard-fails ‚Äî omit the whole subsection instead. EXPECTED to fail: guides carrying the old line (e.g. Amalfi)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TOURS ‚Äî platform group never empty + motion-vs-pickup (Dani 2026-06-16, Azores). (1) EMPTY PLATFORM GROUP: a .tours-group heading (Viator/GetYourGuide/TripAdvisor) must be followed by ‚â•1 üìÖ entry OR the fixed negative-finding line 'No qualifying tours on [Platform] in [City].' before the next group/section end ‚Äî a bare heading with nothing after it hard-fails (Tours ¬ß5+¬ß8). Caught: Azores 'TripAdvisor' heading with nothing after it. (2) MOTION-VS-PICKUP (Tours ¬ß6): üè® ‚Üî üöê / üè® ‚Üê üöê (tour returns to hotel) must ship NO motion banner; üè® ‚Üí üöê (pickup only, ends elsewhere) MUST ship the walk/ride-back row. Motion banner = a row leading üö∂/üöï/üö§."),
    ("2026-06-16", "üöâ ARRIVE BANNER STRICT FORMAT ‚Äî new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16). Closes the gap where a destination üöâ ARRIVE banner's full shape wasn't checked (motion was validated by _validate_motion_row; the ‚Üíhotel closer by _CLOSER_TRAIN_RE). Per Motion Rule ¬ß3b + Icon Order ¬ß4 row 4: 'üöâ ARRIVE {station}: üö∂ N min ¬∑ üöï M min ‚Üí {first stop}'. New check: every .arrive-first div NOT ending in '‚Üí hotel' (i.e. a destination arrival) must carry the station-label+colon, a motion segment (walk[+ride] or ride-only), then '‚Üí {first stop}'. Presence stays a warn (no-transfer days legitimately omit it)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "NO-WIKIPEDIA SENTINEL NOT ABUSABLE ‚Äî new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16: the sentinel was being abused). Links.html ¬ß5 omits the üìñ row ONLY when no substantive English article exists. Abuse pattern: a dedicated English article DOES exist but a <!-- no-wikipedia: --> sentinel was used to dodge the ¬ß3 h1-name-match gate ‚Äî the reason text itself admits it (Quebec City: 'English Wikipedia article title is \"Plains of Abraham\" ‚Äî French name used in guide'). New check (text-only, no network) flags sentinels whose reason concedes a usable EN article ('english wikipedia article title is', 'EN article \"‚Ä¶\" exists', 'wikipedia article title is \"', 'closest is {Article}'); 'only a German/French/es article exists' and 'no ‚Ä¶ article' stay legitimate. EXPECTED to fail: Quebec City (5)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TRAIN TIMETABLE dep/arr SPAN ORDER ‚Äî new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16, Zurich Rhine Falls timetable). Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß4 row 3 is '{dep time} {station} ‚Üí {arr time} {station}', so the first time-span in a .train-time row is the departure (class=\"dep\") and the second is the arrival (class=\"arr\"). Zurich shipped them inverted (8:07am Z√ºrich HB tagged .arr, 8:54am Neuhausen tagged .dep) so the CSS emphasis landed on the wrong time. Dominant convention is dep-first (145 rows) vs 24 inverted (all Zurich). New check: any .train-time row whose first/second dep|arr spans aren't dep,arr hard-fails. EXPECTED to fail: Zurich (24 rows) until the classes are swapped."),
    ("2026-06-24", "HEADS UP ‚Äî entry heading must NOT start with ‚ùóÔ∏è (2026-06-24 per Dani). Icon belongs on section title only. Reversed the 2026-06-17 requirement: hard-fail changed from 'must start with ‚ùóÔ∏è' to 'must NOT start with ‚ùóÔ∏è'. CORE RULES (Heads Up - Extra Section.html ¬ß2) updated to remove ‚ùóÔ∏è from entry format. All 37 affected guides stripped of the icon. Venue-name checks updated to parse _heading_body directly (no longer needs to strip a leading ‚ùóÔ∏è)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "üö´ CLOSED DAYS NEVER STACKED ‚Äî new hard-fail (Dani 2026-06-16: 'üö´ Closed Saturday / üö´ Closed Sunday ‚Äî this needs to fail'). Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß2 Pos 3 + the üèõ note state multiple closed days collapse into ONE üö´ row (range '‚Äì' or '&'), never stacked. The existing üö´ ROW FORMAT check validated each üö´ div independently and the inside-box order check gives üö´ a single rank (equal rank passes), so 2+ stacked üö´ rows shipped silently. New check counts üö´-led rows per operational box (reuses the inside-box order box-walk); >1 in a box hard-fails. EXPECTED to fail: Big Island, Bordeaux, Chicago, Montevideo, Virgin Islands, Zurich (collapse each pair to one '& '/range row)."),
    ("2026-06-16", "TOURS ‚Äî negative-finding line must be the fixed canonical wording (Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß5+¬ß8, added this session at Dani's direction). When a platform group ships no üìÖ tour, its .entry-body line must read exactly 'No qualifying tours on [Platform] in [City].'; whole-section-empty reads 'No qualifying tours in [City].'. Free-form variants (e.g. Lille's 'No qualifying open-group tours on TripAdvisor Experiences for Lille during this build.') hard-fail. Check scans .entry-body blocks in #tours that contain no üìÖ and matches the text against the canonical regex. CORE RULES edited + checksums regenerated + doc_workshop_validator clean."),
    ("2026-06-16", "FOOD DELIVERY ‚Äî link text must be the bare DOMAIN, not the platform name (Dani 2026-06-16: a `Uber Eats`‚Üíubereats.com name-as-link-text entry must fail). The platform name is the .extras-sub heading; the transit-box link row shows the domain (e.g. 'ubereats.com', 'deliveroo.fr'). New check T9c: every <a> text in #food-delivery must match a domain pattern (no spaces, dotted TLD, optional path). Dominant convention 255 domain link-texts vs 22 guides showing the name. NOTE: Food Delivery - Extra Section.html ¬ß2 entry-format text is vague ('[Food App] / [Food Delivery App]') ‚Äî a rule-doc clarification is parked in the To-Do (Rules for Update). EXPECTED to fail: 22 guides incl. Geneva, Rome, Florence, Los Angeles, Scottsdale, Stockholm, Dubai."),
    ("2026-06-16", "HEADS UP ‚Äî note row ‚Ü≥-prefix HARD-FAIL RESTORED. Heads Up ¬ß2 specifies the note line as `‚Ü≥ [Note]`; the 2026-06-10 entry claims ‚Ü≥ enforcement was added for the Heads Up note, but the live check had no ‚Ü≥ requirement (lost in a later edit) and 0 of 32 Heads-Up guides carry it. Re-added: the note row (first body row in the .transit-box, not the Workaround row) must start with ‚Ü≥. Length/capitalisation checks strip the ‚Ü≥ prefix before counting (‚Ü≥ U+21B3 is outside _CG_ICON_RE, so the emoji check is unaffected). EXPECTED: all 32 Heads-Up guides fail until each note row gains its ‚Ü≥."),
    ("2026-06-16", "INSIDE-BOX ICON ORDER check RESTORED (the 2026-06-16 element-order rewrite removed the '(C)/(D)/(E) intra-row order checks', so box rows could ship in any order). Per Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß2 the in-box order is fixed: üéü=1 ¬∑ üèõ/‚è≥=2 ¬∑ üö´=3 ¬∑ üïê/‚è∞=4 ¬∑ üÜì/üíµ=5 ¬∑ ‚öÝÔ∏è=6 ¬∑ üìç=7, and ranks must be non-decreasing down the box. ONLY glyphs ¬ß2 lists for inside the box are ranked; the `üé´ book at` row (Stops Structure ¬ß3c documents it for TRAIN DAYS only ‚Äî its in-box position is undefined) and the guided-tour `üìÖ` lead are left UNRANKED so the legitimate trailing-book-at pattern (Boston/Alaska/Cayman/Curacao) is not penalised. Genuine violations (e.g. a ‚öÝÔ∏è caveat placed above the üèõ hours instead of at pos 6) are flagged."),
    ("2026-06-16", "YELLOW-BOX + BARE OPERATIONAL ROWS HARD-FAILS added (restores enforcement the 2026-06-16 element-order rewrite explicitly deferred ‚Äî 'not enforced here yet, Istanbul/Palm Desert'). TWO checks: (1) every stop-block must carry an operational box (üìç-led .tour-box for no-ticket stops, üéü-led .ticket-box for ticketed) ‚Äî a stop with NO box = 'yellow box missing'; (2) no logistics row sits OUTSIDE the box ‚Äî the full inside-box glyph set üèõ/üèõÔ∏è hours ¬∑ ‚è≥ duration ¬∑ üö´ closed ¬∑ üïê/‚è∞ time ¬∑ üÜì/üíµ cost ¬∑ ‚öÝÔ∏è note ¬∑ üìç address must live INSIDE the box. Both strip box subtrees via _strip_balanced_div first; the glyph must LEAD its row (immediately after a <div> open) so emojis in ‚Ü≥ prose never match. Caught visually by Dani 2026-06-16: Bali Tegallalang / Mount Batur / Uluwatu (bare üèõ/‚è∞/‚öÝÔ∏è/üìç, several with no box at all). The pre-existing 'guided stop has no stop-level üìç' check only covered guided stops; these cover self / ticket / no-box stops too. EXPECTED: Bali fails (6 no-box + 7 bare-row stops) until the rows are wrapped in a box."),
    ("2026-06-16", "‚Ü≥ / üìñ ROW CLASS HARD-FAIL added ‚Äî the ‚Ü≥ description row and üìñ Wikipedia row must carry class=\"stop-row\". Non-canonical classes (Aix-en-Provence shipped stop-desc / stop-wiki) have NO CSS rule, so the rows render with browser-default block margins and the gap before the operational box balloons (caught visually by Dani 2026-06-16, Aix H√¥tel de Caumont). The validator previously had no class check on these rows, so the drift shipped silently. New check flags any <div class=\"‚Ä¶\">‚Ü≥ or üìñ whose class tokens omit `stop-row`; bare class-less box-internal rows (Day Trips transit-box <div>‚Ü≥) are not matched. EXPECTED: Aix fails until its 9 stop-desc + 7 stop-wiki rows are renamed to stop-row."),
    ("2026-06-16", "IN-CITY DAY-CARD SUFFIX CHECK ‚Äî no longer false-positives on em-dashes that are part of a real stop name. The check flagged ANY em-dash `‚Äî` in a non-üéí/non-train overview day-title as a 'city suffix' ‚Äî a rule written for the retired üéí format. Post-2026-06-16 in-city cards are `Day N ‚Äì Stop1 ¬∑ Stop2 ¬∑ ‚Ä¶`, and stop names legitimately contain em-dashes (Lima 'MATE ‚Äî Museo Mario Testino', Lucerne 'Mount Pilatus ‚Äî Golden Round Trip', Marrakech 'Mellah ‚Äî Jewish Quarter', Porto 'Douro River ‚Äî Six Bridges Cruise'). Now: strip the 'Day N ‚Äì' prefix, split the stop list on ' ¬∑ ', and flag an em-dash segment ONLY when it matches no day-block stop name (substring either direction, mirroring the name-sync check). A genuine stray ` ‚Äî City` suffix (matching no stop) is still caught. No guide HTML touched."),
    ("2026-06-16", "DAY-HEADER + OVERVIEW TRAIN-DAY SYNC ‚Äî two checks brought into line with the 2026-06-16 en-dash convention (both had hard-failed every correctly-built train/coach guide). (A) DAY-HEADER locked patterns: the Train Day / Guided Coach patterns required an em-dash `‚Äî` after 'Day N' (`^Day \\d+ ‚Äî Train Day ‚Äî ‚Ä¶`), but all 24 shipped train/coach guides ‚Äî and the overview-day-title convention adopted 2026-06-16 ‚Äî use the en-dash `‚Äì` there. Patterns now accept `[‚Äì‚Äî]` after 'Day N' (Train-Day destination separator stays flexible too). (B) TRIP OVERVIEW stop-count sync: the inline-stops parser grabbed the text after the en-dash even for Train Day cards, turning the 'üöÜ Train Day ‚Äî {Destination}' label into a phantom 1-entry stop list and reporting a count mismatch against the 2-stop day-block. Parser now leaves stops='' when the title contains 'Train Day' (documented intent: Train Day cards carry no inline stop list; the count/name sync skips them). Guided Coach overview cards DO list real stops and are unchanged. No guide HTML touched ‚Äî the guides were correct; the checks were stale."),
    ("2026-06-16", "STOP-BLOCK CANONICAL ELEMENT ORDER ‚Äî corrected (replaces the backwards checks added earlier today). The earlier pass had the order INVERTED vs Stops Structure.html ¬ß3a/¬ß3b: it required the .ticket-box BEFORE the ‚Ü≥ description and forbade the non-guided .tour-box ‚Äî but ¬ß3a/¬ß3b put ‚Ü≥ (Pos 1) and üìñ (Pos 2) FIRST, outside the box, then the operational box (üéü-led .ticket-box for ticketed stops, or the canonical üìç-led .tour-box for no-ticket stops), with üèõ/‚è∞/üìç INSIDE it. Those backwards checks hard-failed all 134 correctly-built guides while passing the box-first shape (Capri/Bali). NOW: (A) the operational box (.ticket-box or .tour-box) must FOLLOW the ‚Ü≥/üìñ rows ‚Äî flags the box-before-description shape (Capri, Bali); (B) ‚Ü≥ (Pos 1) precedes üìñ (Pos 2). The üìç-led .tour-box is recognised as the valid no-ticket logistics box (per _strip_guided_tour_boxes) and no longer flagged. Removed the inverted (A) ticket-box-first check, the (F) no-non-guided-tour-box check, and the box-stripped (C)/(D)/(E) intra-row order checks. NOTE (deferred): bare operational rows outside any box (Istanbul, Palm Desert) are a separate ¬ß3a deviation, not enforced here yet."),
    ("2026-06-16", "ICON REMOVAL hard-fails added: (1) no emoji before Day N in overview-day-title; (2) no inline emoji before stop names in HTML (CSS ::before emptied); (3) no emoji before overview-title text. All three retired 2026-06-16."),
    ("2026-06-16", "NO-ICON-BEFORE checks added: (1) overview-day-title hard-fail when text does not start with 'Day ' (backpack or any icon before day number banned); (2) stop-name inline emoji prefix hard-fail (icon retired from HTML ‚Äî CSS ::before is empty). These complement the existing üéí HTML-ban check."),
    ("2026-06-16", "PILL LABELS updated ‚Äî canonical labels changed: 'Michelin Restaurants' ‚Üí 'Michelin', 'Day Trips by Train' ‚Üí 'Day Trips', 'Stations Near Hotel' ‚Üí 'Train Stations' (overview-extra-link pill text only; section titles unchanged). NEW HARD-FAILS: (1) üéí backpack emoji banned from guide HTML (CSS ::before emptied 2026-06-16); (2) Weekly Closures pill must be preceded by <span style='color:#d4b896;padding:0 6px;...'>|</span> separator. Font: guide-style.css now loads Roboto via Google Fonts @import."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TRIP OVERVIEW TITLE: üìå icon removed from .overview-title (Dani-approved 2026-06-15). All 134 guides updated. Validator: (1) title check updated ‚Äî now requires plain `Trip Overview` with no icon; (2) new hard-fail if üìå detected in .overview-title. Trip Overview.html ¬ßh1 updated. Checksum regenerated."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TITLE PAGE COLOR PALETTE ‚Äî link-color allowlist updated: .title-page .title-address a #ffffff ‚Üí rgba(255,255,255,0.60) (muted white, palette update 2026-06-15)."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TITLE PAGE COLOR PALETTE (Dani-approved): .title-city ‚Üí #f5e0b8 (warm cream); .title-hotel / .title-address / .title-country ‚Üí rgba(255,255,255,0.60) (muted white). Colors set in guide-style.css and Guide Style.css. Validator: new hard-fail check ‚Äî local <style> blocks may not override title color rules with non-canonical values. Buenos Aires local style block removed (now fully covered by guide-style.css)."),
    ("2026-06-15", "TITLE-COUNTRY REQUIRED (Dani-approved): .title-country added to Hotel Banner.html ¬ß1 Entry. Validator updated: (1) expected children list updated from [title-city, title-hotel, title-address] ‚Üí [title-city, title-hotel, title-address, title-country]; (2) new hard-fail check ‚Äî .title-country must be present and non-empty (absent or blank = fail). Guide Style.css + guide-style.css updated: .title-page gains position:relative; .title-country added (absolute, right:16px, vertically centered, uppercase, muted white). All 134 live guides updated with correct country names via script. Validator Index.html, Hotel Banner.html ¬ß1 Entry updated."),
    ("2026-06-15", "Second audit pass ‚Äî 10 fixes: (1) L11332 comment 'rename day-trips-by-train ‚Üí day-trips' was backwards (rename was day-trips ‚Üí day-trips-by-train, 2026-05-26) and had wrong date (2026-05-02). (2) L11362 check label '13-element sequence' ‚Üí '15-element sequence' (eoi_canonical_order grew to 15 with tours + stations-near-hotel addition). (3) L11370 check label '13 canonical anchor ids' ‚Üí '15 canonical anchor ids'. (4) L11310 eoi_canonical_order inline comment 'ships for CA + AZ trips only' ‚Üí 'ships for CA + AZ + OR trips only'. (5) L11317 comment 'two conditional sections (pickleball, heads-up)' ‚Üí 'four conditional sections (pickleball, heads-up, skip-list, day-trips-by-train)'. (6) L11419 T4 check label '10 universal (1‚Äì9 plus Michelin at #11)' ‚Üí '11 universal (1‚Äì10 plus Michelin at #13)'. (7) T5/T6 position labels: pickleball #9 ‚Üí #12, heads-up #11 ‚Üí #14, T5 comment '#10' ‚Üí '#12', T6 comment '#12' ‚Üí '#14'. (8) T5 comment 'CA + AZ' ‚Üí 'CA + AZ + OR'. (9) L11630 skip-list gate used bare substring 'c in trip_city_text' ‚Äî same false-positive risk as 'nice in venice' fixed in Heads Up gate (2026-06-05); fixed to use re.search word-boundary match. (10) L22788 second skip-list city matcher (detailed entry check) also used bare substring; fixed to word-boundary re.search. (11) L12270 _SECTION_IDS for structural </div> balance check was missing 'skip-list' ‚Äî 14 entries, should be 15; skip-list section could have unclosed div and structural check would silently skip it."),
    ("2026-06-15", "CHANGELOG display fixed: CHANGELOG[-5:] ‚Üí CHANGELOG[:5] (L24024). Entries are stored newest-first (prepended); -5 slice was showing the 5 oldest entries, not the 5 most recent. Also: L5948 _row_end_re = re.compile(r'</div>') hoisted before both for-loops in INFORMATION ROWS ARE PLAIN TEXT check ‚Äî was compiled on every hit of every glyph (compiled inside inner for-m loop body). Now compiled once before the outer 'for glyph' loop as _row_end_re; reference updated from row_end_re to _row_end_re. No behaviour change."),
    ("2026-06-15", "DAY TRIPS ‚Äî Island-city ZERO entries hard-fail added (¬ß 2.2, 2026-06-15): _ISLAND_CITIES set covers all island guides system-wide (Capri, Corfu, Azores, Madeira, Iceland, Aruba, Bahamas, Barbados, Cayman Islands, Curacao, Puerto Rico, Sint Maarten, Virgin Islands, Big Island, Kauai, Maui, Oahu). Hard-fail if any extras-sub entry exists in Day Trips for an island city. Azores, Madeira, Iceland moved out of _EUROPEAN_GUIDE_CITIES into _ISLAND_CITIES with exemption comments. Rule home: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß 2.2."),
    ("2026-06-15", "DAY TRIPS ‚Äî European-country MIN 5 HARD FAIL added (Dani-approved). New rule home: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß 4. A guide whose .title-city is in a European country MUST ship ‚â•5 entries in the Day Trips by Train section; below the floor = hard fail. Implemented via a new _EUROPEAN_GUIDE_CITIES set (defined inline next to the check ‚Äî editable, commented per-country) keyed off city_text. Existing rules preserved unchanged: ¬ß 1 'A destination already covered as a Train Day in this guide's itinerary never ships here' (validator: line 16339 Train-Day dedup check, line 17457 destination-conflict check), and the warn-only low-count comment for non-European guides (line 17565). Companion updates same pass: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß 4, Brain/Reference/Rule Dependencies.html (Day Trips icon card), Brain/Reference/Guide Entry Counts.html ¬ß 1, Brain/Reference/Validator Index.html ‚õ≤Ô∏è DAY TRIPS, core_rules_checksums.json regenerated."),
    ("2026-06-15", "12-part validator audit ‚Äî 9 fixes: (1) L330 unused 'import re as _re_wok' removed (re already imported at module level, alias never referenced). (2) L5737-5767 _wr_hours_min_re/_wr_hours_re/_wr_min_re hoisted out of _validate_motion_row and compiled once before the function (were compiled on every call; function called ~hundreds of times per guide run). (3) L8009 _CAP_EXTRA_ICON_RE hoisted out of cappuccino entries loop to before the loop (was compiled on every entry iteration). (4-6) L13039 / L14062 / L14127 / L12743 / L12766 / L12848: 'day-trips' legacy section id replaced with 'day-trips-by-train' in _get_section_html call (Day Trips ‚Ü≥ length check silently never ran), _DIV_BALANCE_SECTIONS (div-balance check silent), _SECTION_ICON_ALLOWLISTS (icon check silent), required_extras tuple + special-case guard (title + empty checks silent), and _SECTION_ICON_MAP (icon check silent). All 5 Day Trips checks were silently skipped on every current guide since the 2026-05-26 rename. (7) L21868 bare_host_pattern = re.compile() inside nested ticket-link loop inlined to re.match() call (no behaviour change). (8-10) Three redundant 'from urllib.parse import unquote as _uqN' inside validate() removed (L18582 _uq2, L18603 _uq3, L23807 _fg_uq) ‚Äî all replaced with the module-level _url_unquote alias. No check logic changed in any fix."),
    ("2026-06-13", "FINAL GATE map-pin check ‚Äî added 'Caribbean Map.html' to _fg_map_names (was 6 continent maps: Europe/US/Asia/Africa/Oceania/South America). The 2026-06-13 Travel-Website reorg introduced Caribbean Map.html as a 7th pin target; the 8 island guides (Aruba, Bahamas, Barbados, Cayman Islands, Curacao, Puerto Rico, Sint Maarten, Virgin Islands) are correctly pinned there but were failing the FINAL GATE because the validator did not scan it. No guide changed ‚Äî gate now scans all 7 maps. Companion updates same pass: guide_tools.py _check_guide_pinned, Navigation.html ¬ß5, Ship Checklist.html ¬ß11, CLAUDE.md DriftyCat."),
    ("2026-06-10", "IN-HOTEL FORMAT rule added to Michelin Restaurants - Extra Section.html ¬ß3 and Cappuccino - Extra Section.html ¬ß3 (mirrors RNH ¬ß5a): when the restaurant/caf√© is inside the guide hotel, use 'üè® In the hotel ¬∑ [Floor]' with no üìç or motion row; Michelin in-hotel entry comes first within its star tier (ride time = 0); Cappuccino in-hotel entry comes first in the section. Validator already handles this via the üè® sentinel (ride_time = 0 for check-D)."),
    ("2026-06-10", "Michelin check J (banned rows) updated: üèõ/üö´ ban now exempts in-hotel entries (¬ß3a legitimately carries üèõ hours and üö´ closed rows); ban still applies to all ¬ß3b standard entries. La Palme d'Or Michelin entry hours fixed: en-dash ‚Üí space-dash-space per üèõ separator rule."),
    ("2026-06-10", "‚Ü≥ prefix enforcement added to all description rows: Shows (was üóí), Day Trips (was üóûÔ∏è), Local Tastes, Getting Around tram, Heads Up note, Stations Near Hotel, Downtown Restaurants, Pickleball ‚Äî all description rows must start with ‚Ü≥; char-limit checks strip ‚Ü≥ before counting. Day Trips _DT_BOX_ALLOWED updated to ('‚Ü≥', 'üé´'). RNH ¬ß5a, ¬ß5b, Michelin ¬ß3a, ¬ß3b, Cappuccino ¬ß3a, ¬ß3b: description rows must start with ‚Ü≥; char-limit checks strip ‚Ü≥ before counting (content after ‚Ü≥ ‚â§80). Michelin and Cappuccino now branch on in-hotel vs standard entry: in-hotel (¬ßa) bans üìç and üö∂/üöï, requires üè® In the hotel ¬∑ [Floor] and üèõ rows; standard (¬ßb) keeps existing address/motion checks. Cappuccino hotel entry excluded from minimum-5 count. La Palme d\'Or Michelin entry in Cannes updated to ¬ß3a format (removed üìç, added floor + hours + closed rows)."),
    ("2026-06-10", "STOP DESCRIPTION ‚Äî üìí retired, ‚Ü≥ now required: stop description row (outside the blue box, Pos 1 per Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß2) switches from üìí to ‚Ü≥, matching all extra-section description rows. Validator: STOP DESCRIPTION LENGTH, ROW FORMAT (no links), and ROW FORMAT (no annotations) checks updated from üìí pattern to ‚Ü≥ pattern. Tour-box containment check updated: 'üìí inside tour-box' ‚Üí '‚Ü≥ inside tour-box'. Shows Cleanliness Check 402 tombstoned (üìí negative-finding row retired ‚Äî negative-finding uses extras-empty class). Guide Style.css and Validator Index updated. Rule files (Icon Order and Format.html, Stops Structure.html) already showed ‚Ü≥ ‚Äî no change needed."),
    ("2026-06-10", "Michelin check-D in-hotel sentinel: 'üè® In the hotel' motion row is now recognised as ride_time = 0 for the within-tier sort key (the restaurant is physically inside the guide hotel). The zero-time hard-fail in _validate_motion_row correctly bans 'üöï 0 min' from appearing in guides, but check D previously treated any missing üöï time as -1 (absent), causing a spurious sort-order failure. Cannes: La Palme d'Or at H√¥tel Martinez updated from 'üö∂ 0 min ¬∑ üöï 0 min' to 'üè® In the hotel'."),
    ("2026-06-11", "CHINA RAIL ‚Äî _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS + omio-required exemption (Dani, Proposal E): added 12306.cn (China Railway national booking platform) to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS ‚Äî Omio has no China coverage, so it was the only valid operator missing from the allowlist. Added _OMIO_EXEMPT_CITIES set (mainland Chinese cities: chongqing, beijing, shanghai, and 17 others) and gated the omio-required check on the guide city not being in that set. CORE RULES companion: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß2 now includes the Omio coverage exception paragraph. No check logic changed for non-China guides."),
    ("2026-06-11", "LINK_COLOR_ALLOWLIST ‚Äî corrected stale hex values for theme-coral, theme-sage, and theme-green toolbar entries. Coral was #1c8a99 (wrong: that is --c-gettingaround-border / teal); corrected to #c85a54 (--c-coral-border). Sage was #8b3520 (wrong: that is --c-closures-border); corrected to #448088 (--c-sage-border). Green was #1c8a99 (wrong); corrected to #5a74c4 (--c-shows-border). All three were introduced with wrong variable mappings at some point after the 2026-05-29 allowlist expansion; the CSS in guide-style.css was always correct. No rule change ‚Äî allowlist now matches the deployed CSS. CHANGELOG label/comment only; check logic unchanged."),
    ("2026-06-10", "üö∂/üöï ZERO-TIME HARD FAIL added to _validate_motion_row: a travel time of 0 min (or 0h / 0h 0min) is never a valid display value ‚Äî use actual measured time or omit the row. Enforced in both the N min path (N==0) and the Xh Ymin / Xh path (total==0). Applies to every motion row across all sections."),
    ("2026-06-06", "DAY TRIPS ‚Äî Train-Day-destination dedup check added (Dani, cross-check item 21): hard fail when a Day Trips by Train extras-sub city matches any Train Day destination parsed from the guide's day-header divs (same extraction as the destination-‚âÝ-guide-city check). Rule home: Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html. EXPECTED: guides whose Day Trips section lists their own Train Day destination now fail until the duplicate entry is removed (Dani: guides failing is fine)."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Stops Structure calibration anchor '¬ß1 food-street anchor (Rue Mouffetard)' RETIRED ‚Äî the market-streets / pedestrian-food-strolls inclusion block was removed from Stops Structure.html ¬ß1b (Dani, cross-check item 7: ¬ß1c markets-of-any-kind exclusion governs without carve-out). The anchor guarded a block that no longer exists."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Skip List.html renamed to Skip List - Extra Section.html (Dani, cross-check item 25 ‚Äî file follows the [Section] - Extra Section.html naming). BUILD_STATE_PHASE_5_MAP value + all labels/comments updated; all guides' build_state.md Phase 5 entries updated in the same pass. No check logic changed."),
    ("2026-06-06", "FOOTNOTE TOOLBAR RETIRED (Dani): the footer sharing link is retired for now and must not be used in the guides. Guides/toolbar.js now carries FOOTNOTE_RETIRED = true and never auto-loads footnote.js (loader kept behind the guard for re-enable). TB-9 rewritten: guide loads toolbar.js + no inline footer div + no direct footnote.js script tag. TB-11 rewritten: was footnote.js structure check; now verifies the FOOTNOTE_RETIRED guard is present and true in Guides/toolbar.js. footnote.js stays on disk, unused. Rule updated: Brain/Reference/Toolbar.html ¬ß6 (Retired) + Navigation.html ¬ß1 + Rules for Claude.html ¬ß4 publishing note (approved CORE RULES edit; checksums regenerated)."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Deep-audit decision 3 (Dani): klook.com REMOVED from _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS ‚Äî Klook is an attractions/tours aggregator, not a train booking site; any Klook URL (incl. tour pages) passed the Day Trips operator gate. Rail bookings must use the actual operator site."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Deep-audit decision 2 (Dani): üí∞ CURRENCY FORMAT block RETIRED (trailing-USD label check + non-USD symbol drift-catcher). It cited a Stops Structure price rule that no longer exists; the live rule is DriftyCat zero-money ('no $ ‚Ç¨ ¬£ ¬•, no ISO codes ‚Äî ever'), already enforced by the global ZERO-CURRENCY check. Both sub-checks could only pass vacuously. Single source of truth: one global check, prices/currency banned everywhere."),
    ("2026-06-10", "STRUCTURAL check added: every extras-section div must have a matching closing </div>. Detected via _walk_balanced_div ‚Äî if end_index == len(html) the div was never closed. Covers all 14 section IDs (weekly-closures, tours, cappuccino, restaurants, michelin, downtown, local-tastes, food-delivery, shows, getting-around, stations-near-hotel, day-trips, pickleball, heads-up). A missing </div> nests all downstream sections inside the unclosed one, breaking mobile CSS layout. Hard-fail. 54 guides fixed (42 in prior session + 12 remaining getting-around sections)."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Deep-audit decision 1 (Dani): two always-pass reminder check()s converted to warn() ‚Äî Getting Around 'ride app availability confirmed via web search' and Food Delivery 'platform availability confirmed via web search'. An unconditional ‚úÖ asserted verification that never happened and inflated the pass count. Now ‚öÝÔ∏è warnings, suppressible via <!-- warn-ok: ride-app-search --> / <!-- warn-ok: food-delivery-search --> once confirmed."),
    ("2026-06-06", "CITATION REFRESH (CORE RULES audit): stale ¬ß citations corrected in check labels and comments ‚Äî Train Day quota checks now cite Day Structure.html ¬ß6 (was Stops Structure.html ¬ß5; the quota rule lives in Day Structure), üé´ train-header row checks + train-modifier comments now cite Stops Structure.html ¬ß3c (was ¬ß5 ‚Äî renumbered by the 2026-05-26 file consolidation). No check logic changed ‚Äî labels and comments only. Companion: brain_check.py gained check_section_citation_targets() (warn-mode) to catch future ¬ß renumbering drift."),
    ("2026-06-15", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added elron.ee to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Elron ‚Äî Estonia's national rail operator; Tallinn build, covers Tallinn‚ÄìTartu, Tallinn‚ÄìNarva, Tallinn‚ÄìP√§rnu, Tallinn‚ÄìPaldiski lines). Omio covers Estonia, so the 'or omio' suffix stands."),
    ("2026-06-15", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added croatiarailways.hr to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Hrvatske ≈æeljeznice ‚Äî Croatia's national rail operator; Split build, covers Split‚Äì≈Ýibenik‚ÄìKnin‚ÄìZagreb main line). Omio covers Croatia, so the 'or omio' suffix stands."),
    ("2026-06-12", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added metlink.org.nz to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Metlink ‚Äî Greater Wellington regional rail operator: KƒÅpiti / Hutt Valley / Wairarapa lines; Wellington build, same pattern as the gotransit / sunrail / gobrightline additions). Omio covers NZ, so the 'or omio' suffix stands and Wellington is NOT added to _OMIO_EXEMPT_CITIES."),
    ("2026-06-12", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added sz.si / potniski.sz.si / slo-zeleznice.si to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Slovenske ≈æeleznice ‚Äî Slovenia's national rail operator; Ljubljana build, same pattern as the gotransit / sunrail additions). Omio covers Slovenia, so the 'or omio' suffix stands."),
    ("2026-06-07", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added gotransit.com to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (GO Transit/Metrolinx ‚Äî Ontario regional rail operator, Toronto-Niagara Falls route; Toronto build, same pattern as the 2026-06-06 sunrail/gobrightline addition)"),
    ("2026-06-06", "Day Trips operator allowlist: added sunrail.com + gobrightline.com to _TRAIN_TICKET_HOSTS (Florida commuter/intercity rail operators ‚Äî Orlando build)"),
    ("2026-06-06", "FINAL GATE ‚Äî ‚ùì OPEN QUESTIONS PARKING GATE added (Dani): at the end of validation the guide hard-fails if To Do List ‚ùì Open Questions holds an entry naming this guide's city that is NOT a CORE RULES fix/edit/proposal question (detected by core rules / rules for update / rules for claude tokens). The build crib makes every other call itself and documents it (decisions log / build sentinels) ‚Äî ‚ùì is reserved for CORE RULES questions only. Scoped per-city so one crib's parked question never blocks another crib's build."),
    ("2026-06-06", "üìç HOME-CITY-IN-DISPLAY check ‚Äî street-name carve-out (Miami build). The check substring-matched the home city anywhere in the anchor text, so '3251 S Miami Ave ¬∑ Coconut Grove' hard-failed for the Miami guide even though the rule (Links.html ¬ß6) bans the redundant city SUFFIX, not street names that contain the city word. Now a word-boundary match that ignores the home-city token when immediately followed by a street suffix (Ave/St/Blvd/Rd/Dr/Way/Ln/Ct/Hwy/Pkwy/Ter/Pl/Sq and long forms). A standalone trailing city ('‚Ä¶ ¬∑ Miami') still fails."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Overview extras sync check B aligned with Trip Overview.html ¬ß3: the ‚ú® Claude Inspiration pill is no longer flagged as an orphan when the claude-inspiration div exists (it is not an extras-section by design ‚Äî Claude Inspiration - Extra Section.html ¬ß4). Pill stays optional: check A unchanged, guides without the pill still pass. First shipped on Corfu v1."),
    ("2026-06-05", "üö§ CAR-FREE CITY RIDE GLYPH added (Dani-approved, Option B). New CORE RULES rule: cities with no road network (CAR_FREE_CITIES = {'venice'}) use üö§ (water-taxi) instead of üöï in every motion banner + from-hotel row (Motion Rule.html ¬ß1, Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß2 row 8f). Validator: a single enforcement check runs on raw html (car-free ‚Üí üöï must not appear outside Getting Around; road city ‚Üí üö§ must not appear at all), then üö§ is normalised to üöï so every existing ride check ‚Äî closer format, RNH/Cappuccino/Stations motion rows, Michelin check-D ride parse + within-tier sort, Tours üö∂/üöï ‚Äî validates üö§ with the identical format/time/order rules as üöï (no per-check edits needed). Migrated Venice (25 motion rows üöï‚Üíüö§; Getting Around 'üöï Ride Apps' heading retained). Verified Venice 0 failures."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Michelin check-D ride parser extended to read Motion-Rule time formats. The old parser ('üöï[^0-9]{0,15}(\\d+)\\s*min') only recognised the 'N min' form and reported any hours-format ride ('üöï 1h 7min') as a missing üöï time ‚Äî failing check D on cross-city guides whose Michelin venues are ‚â•60 min away (surfaced on Palo Alto: hotel in Mountain View, all 5 starred venues in San Francisco). Now parses 'N min', 'Xh Ymin' and 'Xh' to total minutes, matching Motion Rule ¬ß1's enforced format. Working-surface fix during the item-17 backfill; no rule change. Verified Palo Alto 685/0."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Links ¬ß3 staleness reconciled (To Do List item 19, Dani). Dead _log_entry_age helper removed ‚Äî the 30‚Äì90-day WARN tier was retired 2026-05-27 (a logged PASS now permanently suppresses the warning, no age expiry), so the helper was never called. Links.html ¬ß3 rule text updated to match: 'Logged PASS ‚Üí green (permanent, no expiry); Missing/non-PASS ‚Üí WARN'. No behavior change ‚Äî helper was already dead."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Michelin within-tier order FLIPPED alphabetical ‚Üí closest-to-hotel first by üöï ride time (To Do List item 17, Dani). Michelin entries now carry a üö∂ N min ¬∑ üöï N min ‚Üí hotel motion row (Michelin Restaurants - Extra Section.html ¬ß3 updated); check D parses the üöï minutes and enforces non-decreasing order within each star tier, hard-failing when a tier is out of order OR any entry lacks the üöï from-hotel time. FIXED a latent parser bug: the audit block read stars from .entry-body row 1, but Style A (locked 2026-05-19) puts ‚≠ê+name on the .extras-sub heading ‚Äî so entries_audit was ALWAYS empty on current guides and checks B/D/E/F/H/I/J/L/N ran vacuously. Now reads stars from the preceding .extras-sub heading; cuisine region = box-start‚Üíüìç. J banned-rows updated: üö∂/üöï removed from the ban (now required), üèõ/üö´ still banned. EXPECTED: all 50 guides with a Michelin section now fail check D until the üöï from-hotel times are backfilled per entry."),
    ("2026-06-05", "A4 follow-up (Dani) ‚Äî NEW global hard-fail: any bare ‚ùó (U+2757 not followed by U+FE0F) anywhere in a guide fails (regex ‚ùó(?!Ô∏è) over full html, including comments). Guarantees every ‚ùó ‚Äî pill, section title, and each entry marker ‚Äî uses +VS16; bare entries previously slipped through (entry parser startswith('‚ùóÔ∏è ') silently skipped them). Caught + fixed a bare ‚ùó in Berlin's '<!-- ‚ùó HEADS UP -->' build comment. All guides re-swept: zero bare ‚ùó remain."),
    ("2026-06-05", "A4 (To Do List) ‚Äî Heads Up icon glyph unified to +VS16 per Dani. Title check (_cg_title_exact) flipped from bare '‚ùó Heads Up' to '‚ùóÔ∏è Heads Up' (U+2757+FE0F); comment + fail messages updated; pill expected-label map and icon-map check display string updated to +VS16 (pill compare already FE0F-normalized, so cosmetic). Entry parser unchanged (already required +VS16). CORE RULES docs (Trip Overview pill, Heads Up <h1> title) and all 16 guides carrying a Heads Up section migrated bare‚Üí+VS16; re-validated ‚Äî title check passes, no Heads-Up-related failures introduced."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Deep-audit fix pass (Lane 1-5, non-CORE-RULES items). LANE 1: closer-format + logistic-row-parenthetical checks now match div bodies tolerant of inline markup (the old [^<]* grab skipped any row with a <strong>/<a>, a false negative); STOP_TYPE_ICONS gained bare üéü; _day_idx prefix branch guarded to len>=3; pill-label compare FE0F-normalized; closer-format LABEL corrected to match regex+rule (ride-only üöï valid when walk>40min). LANE 2: T_NEW5 relaxed to any lowercase theme token (¬ß2 'choose freely'); NEW T_NEW8 ‚Äî CI title icon must not reuse a section-header icon (¬ß2). (CI pill-label enforcement deliberately NOT added ‚Äî unresolved fixed-vs-free contradiction parked in To Do List.) LANE 3: removed 2 dead always-pass checks (Day Trips 'always allowed', Day Trips 'section present'); collapsed 41 mislabeled Heads-Up 'section absent' placeholders (fired on spec-file-unreadable) to one honest line. LANE 5: Count Reference.html -> Guide Entry Counts.html in all check labels/comments. Verified via golden-master harness ‚Äî only intended output changes, no new guide failures."),
    ("2026-06-05", "REMOVED idx-coverage-all check (the 'all guide folders listed in Guides-Index.html' check / former Check B) ‚Äî it scanned every Guides/ folder and hard-failed the guide under test whenever ANY sibling guide's HTML was absent from Guides-Index.html. With multiple cribs building guides concurrently, a sibling's in-progress or not-yet-indexed build is routinely present, so this check cross-failed essentially every guide for a condition the current guide cannot control. Index coverage is now fully self-scoped: idx-coverage-self (Check A, retained) verifies THIS guide is indexed, and guide_tools.py ship gate (_check_guide_indexed) enforces it at ship time per crib (per the 2026-06-02 'each crib checks only its own guide' decision). Empty _build-only folders never triggered the removed check (no top-level HTML); the trigger was always a concurrent shipped-but-unindexed sibling. Validator Index.html updated."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Robustness fix (validator audit): results.clear() added at the top of validate() ‚Äî the module-level results list was never reset, so a second in-process validate() call would accumulate the prior run's entries and double-count the pass/fail/warn tally. Harmless under CLI single-call use; closes the latent bug for any future import/reuse. No check logic changed; _warn_ok_tags already reset at top of validate()."),
    ("2026-06-02", "Validator fix: _idx_hrefs uses dest-card class (was overview-day ‚Äî guides_index was redesigned to use dest-card); map lookup now checks Trip-Essentials/Maps/ first; _INDEX_EXCLUDED_GUIDES emptied (Copenhagen + Edinburgh shipped)."),
    ("2026-06-02", "MAP PIN check added: FAIL if the guide's city name is not present as a PINS entry in Trip-Essentials/Europe Map.html or Trip-Essentials/US Map.html. Enforces Navigation.html ¬ß 5 step 5 (map pin rule added 2026-06-02). Check runs after the GUIDES INDEX coverage check. Companion changes: guide_tools.py ship gate (_check_guide_pinned), CLAUDE.md DriftyCat, Navigation.html ¬ß 5, Ship Checklist.html ¬ß 11, Validator Index.html."),
    ("2026-06-02", "BUILD_STATE_PHASE_1: 'Capabilities' renamed to 'Connectors.html' ‚Äî guide_tools.py init already emitted 'Connectors.html'; validator was still checking the old name, causing a Phase 1 fail on any guide built via init. All existing build_state.md files updated in the same pass."),
    ("2026-06-02", "Phase 1+2 early exit: _bs_phase_check now returns bool; if Phase 1 or Phase 2 unchecked, validator halts immediately with a loud banner listing which files are missing/unchecked and exits with code 2. Running 500+ checks on invented-format HTML is noise ‚Äî halt forces the reads first."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Editorial drift words banned from guide content and CORE RULES note spans: 'vibe', 'contactless', 'fastest way', 'worth the trip/a visit/it', 'worth crossing' added to _HEDGE_PATTERNS (hard-fail in shipped guides); 'vibe', 'worth', 'ticket info', 'kind of experience', 'character' added to _CR_NOTE_BANNED_WORDS (hard-fail in CORE RULES <span class=\"note\"> annotations). Companion rule edits: 'kind of experience' removed from Getting Around, Icon Order, Tours; 'ticket info' removed from Getting Around, Icon Order; 'vibe', 'and character', 'why it worth the trip', 'the surprise', 'route/stops/line details' removed from all description note spans across Pickleball, Downtown Restaurants, Heads Up, Day Trips by Train. London metro description to be fixed (contactless + fastest way)."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Local Tastes calibration anchor updated: '¬ß2 Google Maps link anchor' ‚Üí '¬ß2 location anchor' (needle 'Google Maps' ‚Üí 'goes to its location') ‚Äî Local Tastes spec text changed from 'is a Google Maps link' to 'goes to its location' as part of Maps/Link word ban."),
    ("2026-05-27", '"Map"/"Maps" bare visible text banned globally ‚Äî any text node containing the word Map or Maps (case-insensitive, singular or plural) now hard-fails. Extends the existing <a>Maps</a> link-text check to cover all visible text drift (e.g. "Address [Maps]"). Per Icon Order and Format.html row 7 ‚Äî address IS the link, the word Map/Maps never appears as guide text.'),
