    ("2026-05-19", "Link styling C: inline style='text-decoration:...' on <a> tags now fails ‚Äî link styling is CSS-only"),
    ("2026-05-19", "CORE RULES content: banned annotation phrases ('‚Üí heading row', 'first/last row of body box', 'body box') now fail ‚Äî layout notes are not rules"),
    ("2026-05-19", "üö´ row capitalisation: 'closed' (lowercase) now fails ‚Äî must be 'Closed' with capital C"),
    ("2026-05-19", "üóìÔ∏è Weekly Closures: 'Closed' must be capitalised ‚Äî flipped WC-X1 and format regex to require capital C, fail lowercase"),
    ("2026-05-19", "üóìÔ∏è Weekly Closures: separator changed from em-dash to ¬∑ ‚Äî format is now 'Category ¬∑ Closed Day'; validator and all guides updated"),
    ("2026-05-19", "üóìÔ∏è Weekly Closures: WC-X4 extended ‚Äî all words in category name must be title-cased, not just the first; '&' exempt"),
    ("2026-05-19", "üìç Maps link: home city in display text now fails ‚Äî city belongs in URL query only; different city allowed for out-of-city stops"),
    ("2026-05-20", "‚≠ê star spacing REVERSED (supersedes 2026-05-19): rating is tight N.N‚≠ê, no space before ‚≠ê ‚Äî '4.8‚≠ê' not '4.8 ‚≠ê'. New global check fails any decimal rating with a space before the star. Rules (venue review-link, Tours, Tickets) all use tight; newest rule prevails."),
    ("2026-05-20", "üìÖ Tours: added as Extras section (after Weekly Closures) ‚Äî section enums, entry-format / rating-bar / per-platform-minimum checks. _TOURS_MINIMUM_EXEMPT rollout exemption removed 2026-06-02 (all guides fixed)"),
    ("2026-05-21", "üéü Tours flat-format check: hard FAIL if any .tour-box wrapper found inside #tours extras-section ‚Äî Tours entries must use flat Iceland layout (plain divs in .entry-body); nested .tour-box = double background + retired format"),
    ("2026-05-23", "Getting Around ¬ß2b tram description row enforced ‚Äî first row of tram transit-box must be ‚â§80 char service description, not the template line; hard fail when missing"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Getting Around ¬ß2b tram description row cap raised to ‚â§160 chars (2 lines max) ‚Äî rule updated in Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß3"),
    ("2026-05-23", "warn-ok sentinel system: every ‚öÝÔ∏è warning now instructs guide to add <!-- warn-ok: TAG reason --> comment to document why it is acceptable; tram-not-planned check added ‚Äî warns when Getting Around lists üöé Tram but no tram rows in itinerary"),
    ("2026-05-24", "‚õ≤Ô∏è Day Trips by Train üé´ aggregator guard: Viator/GYG/TripAdvisor links in Day Trips üé´ rows now fail ‚Äî booking must go to the transport operator (train/bus/transfer site), not a guided-tour aggregator (Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß2)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üöó Food Delivery transit-box link-only tightened: description text mixed into the URL link div now fails ‚Äî link div must contain ONLY <a href=...>; no surrounding prose (Food Delivery - Extra Section.html ¬ß2)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üöï Getting Around per-app ride-app transit-box link-only check ‚Äî each üöï extras-sub transit-box must have exactly 1 child div (operator link); description rows fail (¬ß1b gap: prior checks only matched 'Ride App' heading, missed per-app üöï Grab / üöï Gojek format)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Getting Around stale code audit: (1) tram description check comment + error message corrected from '‚â§80 chars' to '‚â§160 chars' (cap was raised 2026-05-24 but comment was not updated); (2) retired comment claiming 'description div BETWEEN heading and transit-box is by design' corrected ‚Äî that intermediate format was retired 2026-05-24 and the gap check (added 2026-05-25) explicitly bans it; (3) two stale old-format check labels that said 'description (‚â§80 chars)' updated to reflect no-description rule (¬ß1b)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöï Getting Around intermediate description div gap fixed ‚Äî description div placed BETWEEN the üöï extras-sub and the transit-box was invisible to the transit-box child-div count check; new gap check strips comments and hard-fails on any non-whitespace <div> in that space (¬ß1b: no description row)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "‚òï Cappuccino audit ‚Äî two new checks added: (F) annotation leakage ([UPDATE]/[CHECK]/üî¥/[TBD] etc. in heading or entry body hard-fail, same pattern as DR/RNH/Shows); (G) duplicate caf√© names within the section (copy-paste error, same pattern as DR/WC/Michelin). Coverage fixed: 'maximum 5' claim removed (CORE RULES has no maximum cap); 'No build annotations' coverage item now accurately reflects enforcement (was false-yes before this session)."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel audit ‚Äî entry count check added: 3+ entries now hard-fail per ¬ß 2 (one local/regional + one high-speed; same station = 1 combined entry; Coverage said 'yes' but no check existed ‚Äî false-yes fixed). Coverage updated: added 'bus station entries' and 'üéü aggregator booking link' items that were enforced in validator but not documented; entry count item now accurately reflects enforcement."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üçÆ Local Tastes audit ‚Äî K2 text check added: 'What it is' / 'Where to find it' visible labels are now caught directly in the Local Tastes entry loop (previously only the CSS class .local-tastes-list was caught via global DRIFT SENTINELS; text labels themselves were not caught). Coverage updated: (1) K2 item clarified to reflect both class and text checks; (2) added 9 new 'yes' items that were enforced in the validator but not documented in Coverage: NAME annotations, üìç annotations, NAME not generic, NAME ‚â§50 chars, entry count ‚â§6, extras-empty for negative-finding, structural drift block, section div resolved, spec drift protection."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöó Food Delivery audit ‚Äî 5 fixes: (1) _fd_inner/_fd_is_negative de-duplicated ‚Äî _walk_balanced_div was called twice (T9a + T9b); now pre-computed once after _fd_hdr; (2) ¬ß 2 preference order check added ‚Äî DoorDash/Uber Eats (tier 1) ‚Üí Grubhub (tier 2) ‚Üí local (tier 3); entries out of tier order now hard-fail; (3) annotation leakage check updated ‚Äî description row removed 2026-05-24 (¬ß3) but check still indexed into _fdtb_child_divs[1] (which no longer exists); simplified to scan full transit-box body; print label + check label updated from 'description' to 'transit-box'; (4) web search reminder moved from Getting Around block (keyed off getting-around section) to Food Delivery block (keyed off _fd_hdr) ‚Äî logically correct placement; (5) stale comment at negative-finding check updated ('set in T9a/T9b blocks above' ‚Üí 'set in pre-computation block above')."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöï Getting Around dead code removed ‚Äî two old-format checks that looked for class='ride-app' elements and a single 'Ride App' extras-sub heading were retired: (1) RIDE-APP NAME ROW SHAPE ENFORCEMENT (checked class='ride-app' + <strong> on name rows ‚Äî passed vacuously since 2026-05-24 when per-app format replaced single-block); (2) RIDE APPS ‚Äî ENTRY FORMAT CHECK (checked old 3-row name+description+link pattern per class='ride-app' entry ‚Äî also vacuous since 2026-05-24); (3) RIDE-APP SUBHEADING EXACT TEXT (checked heading was exactly 'üöï Ride App' singular ‚Äî vacuous since per-app headings use app names like 'üöï Uber', not 'Ride App'). All three passed vacuously on every current guide."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Rule 401 ‚Äî Motion format: ‚â•60 min bare 'N min' is now a hard-FAIL in _validate_motion_row (üö∂/üöï segments). The Xh Ymin / Xh check already existed (lines ~4886‚Äì4900); the time-stripping step that silently swallowed times after From Hotel: was removed (line 4859 retired ‚Äî Rule 402). 41 lines fixed across 9 guides before the validator check landed."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Rule 402 ‚Äî From Hotel departure time banned: retired 'TRAIN DAY OPENER ‚Äî departure time inline' (which required H:MM am in train-day From Hotel lines) and replaced with hard-FAIL check 'From Hotel ‚Äî no departure time' that fires on ANY .hotel-first div containing a time pattern. 12 lines fixed across 8 guides (Paris 3, Munich 4, Sydney, Lisbon, Turin, London, SF 1 each). Motion rule time-strip at line 4859 also removed so times are no longer silently tolerated during pattern validation."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üö© Flag Rows deep-clean ‚Äî 8 label/comment fixes: (1) ‚è∞ format check: added missing 'Pos 4b' citation (Icon Order and Format.html); (2) üö´ format check: added missing 'Pos 3' citation; (3) üÜì format check: added missing 'Pos 5a' citation; (4) üíµ format check: added missing 'Pos 5b' citation; (5) ‚öÝÔ∏è format check: added missing 'Pos 6' citation; (6‚Äì7) two üìÖ format checks: removed wrong 'Pos 1' citations (Pos 1 = üéü ticket, not üìÖ) ‚Äî replaced with drift-guard note (guided-tour format retired 2026-05-20); (8) B1 comment inside STOP FLAGS ‚Äî LOCATION updated from stale 'Guided tour box ‚Äî flags forbidden' to explicit drift-guard explanation noting the .tour-box with üìÖ lead is a retired-format artifact."),
    ("2026-05-24", "üéü ticket-box <strong> check: fixed scoping bug ‚Äî if-checks for missing/over-bold <strong> were outside the inner for-tsm loop (only last match per ticket-box was ever evaluated); moved inside the loop so every üéü link is checked"),
    ("2026-05-24", 'Tours ‚Äî motion row banned suffix: "‚Üí from hotel" must not appear in a tour entry body; correct format is üö∂ N min ¬∑ üöï N min only with no directional label (Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß4)'),
    ("2026-05-24", 'Tours ‚Äî "time from hotel" template leakage: hard FAIL if the literal phrase "time from hotel" appears anywhere in the Tours section ‚Äî it is a builder instruction in Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß4 and must be replaced with actual üö∂/üöï values before shipping'),
    ("2026-05-24", "Banned tour-type synonyms added: cycling tour/tours, bicycle tour/tours, cycle tour/tours (bike tour synonyms); culinary tour/tours, tasting tour/tours, gastro tour/tours (food tour synonyms); e-bike tour/tours, ebike tour/tours (e-bike ban ‚Äî Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß2)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Banned tour-type standalone terms added: 'bike', 'e-bike', 'ebike', 'e bike', 'electric bike', 'bicycle' ‚Äî any tour entry containing these words now hard-fails regardless of whether 'tour' follows. Tours section collector updated: now scans <strong> text (tour name only); falls back to <a> text only when <strong> absent."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Wikipedia URL ‚öÝÔ∏è suppression ‚Äî bug fix: verify_booking_links.py now writes h1 PASS results into verification_log.json (platform: wikipedia, method: live_fetch, result: PASS) after each live check. Previously h1-match results were printed but never persisted, so the validator's suppression logic could never find a Wikipedia PASS entry and the ‚öÝÔ∏è never cleared. Fix: future_to_item dict replaces zip(futures, h1_required) to correctly map as_completed futures back to their source items; PASS entries written to _build/verification_log.json (creating the file + _meta block if absent)."),
    ("2026-05-27", "Wikipedia URL ‚öÝÔ∏è suppression ‚Äî 90-day expiry removed: a PASS entry in verification_log.json (platform: wikipedia, result: PASS) now permanently suppresses the ‚öÝÔ∏è for that URL. Previously a logged PASS expired after 90 days and re-triggered the warning; that re-expiry check (_log_entry_age <= 90) is removed. Warning now fires only for URLs never logged as PASS."),
    ("2026-05-27", '"private" keyword check ‚Äî moved from Stops Structure (full-guide text scan, warn) to Tours section block (Tours extras-section only, hard fail). Old check scanned all visible text guide-wide and issued a warning; new check scans only _tours_inner (the Tours extras-section HTML) and calls check() ‚Äî hard fail when "private" appears in the Tours section. Validator Coverage updated: warn ‚Üí yes, description updated to reflect Tours-only scope. Guides that had "private" outside the Tours section (e.g. in a map label or prose) no longer trigger.'),
    ("2026-05-26", "Tours extras-sub format enforcement (Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß6): (1) ts_name_not_strong ‚Äî tour name must be first child of <a> wrapped in <strong>; (2) ts_not_encapsulated ‚Äî platform ¬∑ rating ¬∑ reviews must be inside <a>, no text after </a>. Canonical: üìÖ N. <a><strong>Name</strong> ¬∑ Platform ¬∑ N.N‚≠ê ¬∑ NNN+ reviews</a>. Both are hard fails."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöä Metro description ‚â§80 char check now enforced unconditionally ‚Äî previously skipped when transit-box shape was wrong (not exactly 3 child divs); now runs on the first child div regardless of total count, so a >80 char description always hard-fails even when the shape check also fires."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Tours city rule ‚Äî tour must be held in or depart from the guide city (Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß1 City rule, added 2026-05-24). Check: tours without üè® pickup icon must have üìç in guide city; tours with üè® pickup from a different city fail. Enforced on extras-sub entries in the Tours section."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Tours motion row: üöï-only now accepted when meeting point is >40 min walk from hotel (Motion Rule already allows this for banners; Tours check now matches)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Claude Inspiration T1: Skip List footnote (id=skip-list) may follow Inspiration ‚Äî it is still last among sections; only non-skip-list extras-sections after CI now fail"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Count minimums now WARN, never hard-fail (per Dani): Cappuccino ‚â•5, Restaurants Near Hotel ‚â•5, Downtown Restaurants ‚â•5, Tours ‚â•5-per-platform, and Tours walking-tours ‚â•2 no longer FAIL when below the target ‚Äî genuinely small markets ship what qualifies and document why in the <!-- low-count: [reason] --> comment. A below-minimum section warns; a below-minimum section MISSING its low-count comment also only warns (nudge). Mirrors the Day Trips low-count model. NOTE: only count MINIMUMS were softened ‚Äî structural integrity floors (‚â•1 tour-box, ‚â•1 ticket-box, ‚â•1 overview-day, ‚â•1 üèõ row per stop-block), per-entry quality bars (Tours 4.5‚≠ê/6-reviews), and the walking-tours MAXIMUM-4 cap remain hard fails."),
    ("2026-05-24", "ü´ï Restaurants Near Hotel suffix check: cuisine or any plain text after the review link in extras-sub now fails ‚Äî heading format is [Restaurant] ¬∑ [review link] only; cuisine belongs on line 2 of entry-body (Restaurants Near Hotel - Extra Section.html ¬ß 5b)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üçΩÔ∏è Downtown Restaurants suffix check: cuisine or any plain text after the review link in extras-sub now fails ‚Äî heading format is [Restaurant] ¬∑ [review link] only; cuisine belongs on line 2 of entry-body (Downtown Restaurants - Extra Section.html ¬ß 6)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "‚òï Cappuccino suffix check (T4d): any plain text after the review link in extras-sub now fails ‚Äî heading format is [Caf√©] ¬∑ [review link] only (Cappuccino - Extra Section.html ¬ß 3)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Section title enforcement tightened: 'Restaurants Near Hotel' ‚Äî bare 'Restaurants' alias removed, only 'ü´ï Restaurants Near Hotel' accepted; 'Downtown Restaurants' ‚Äî bare 'Downtown' alias removed, only 'üçΩÔ∏è Downtown Restaurants' accepted. Wrong titles now hard-fail."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Section title enforcement ‚Äî all sections: canonical title added as comment under each required_extras entry; 'üé≠ Shows' alias removed ‚Äî only 'üé≠ Shows, Performances & Concerts' accepted; all other section titles verified exact against their rules files. Hard-fail on any deviation."),
    ("2026-05-24", "Section renames applied everywhere: 'Stations Near the Hotel' ‚Üí 'Train Stations Near Hotel', 'Near the Hotel' ‚Üí 'Restaurants Near Hotel'; required_extras regex patterns updated to match new canonical titles"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üéü Free hard fail: any üéü div containing 'free', 'no booking', or 'no reservation' now fails ‚Äî only üÜì may mark a free/no-booking venue; 'üéü Free ‚Äî no booking needed' is always wrong (locked 2026-05-24 ‚Äî Marrakech Jemaa el-Fnaa drift)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî bus station entries: any extras-sub whose name contains 'bus' must follow train-station format (station-box wrapper + üìç address + motion row); hard fail on any missing element (locked 2026-05-24)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî üéü booking link aggregator guard: any üéü row in #stations-near-hotel must link to the rail/bus operator, not Viator / Get Your Guide / TripAdvisor / any 'tours' site ‚Äî hard fail (locked 2026-05-24)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Food review link domain check: class='review-link' href in Cappuccino / Restaurants Near Hotel / Downtown Restaurants must point to Yelp, Google Reviews, or Local Guide ‚Äî not venue's own site, not Viator, not TripAdvisor (Cappuccino ¬ß 3 / RNH ¬ß 4b / Downtown ¬ß 5, locked 2026-05-24)"),
    ("2026-05-24", "Train Day ‚Äî üé´ booking row now required on BOTH outbound and return train-headers: every üöä/üöÑ train-header must carry a üé´ book at: [Train Ticket Operator] row between the header and div.train; old check that required the return to NOT have üé´ is retired; Stops Structure.html ¬ß5 return block updated to include üé´ row"),
    ("2026-05-24", "üöó Food Delivery false positive fixed: embedded \\x08 backspace byte in regex <a[^>]*> corrupted it to <a\\x08[^>]*> (then to <a[[^>]*> after partial repair) ‚Äî <a> stripping never matched so link text was left behind as 'description text'; fixed to correct <a[^>]*>.*?</a>"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Trip Overview icon-sync: .guided modifier retired 2026-05-20 ‚Äî stale mixed/guided branches removed; any .stop-name.guided class now hard-fails regardless of mixed or pure day (Stops Structure.html ¬ß2 ‚Äî only üéí Self-Guided and üöÜ Train Day are active)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Trip Overview extras pills canonical order check added: .overview-extra-link pill hrefs must appear in the same relative sequence as eoi_canonical_order (Guide Structure.html / Trip Overview.html ¬ß3); out-of-order pills now hard-fail"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Tours ¬ß1 city rule ‚Äî not automatable: ¬ß6 address format omits the guide city from local addresses (street + neighborhood only), so absence of the city name in üìç text is always correct, not a violation; rule must be enforced at build time (‚ùå human in Validator Coverage)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Tours ¬ß1 walking tour cap added: guide must have minimum 2 and maximum 4 walking tours across all platforms combined (counted by 'walking' in extras-sub name); hard-fail outside the 2‚Äì4 range"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Downtown Restaurants dead postal-code code removed: _DR_POSTAL_RE compile + dr_no_postal_code population were dead since 2026-05-19 rule reversal; declaration and entry-loop code cleaned up"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Downtown Restaurants inverse negative-finding check added (E-inv): when entries are present, 'No restaurants in downtown [City].' must NOT appear ‚Äî same pattern as Cappuccino / Day Trips / Pickleball inverse checks"),
    ("2026-05-25", "ü´ï Restaurants Near Hotel stale-label cleanup: section header/print renamed NEAR THE HOTEL ‚Üí RESTAURANTS NEAR HOTEL; all ¬ß4a ‚Üí ¬ß5a and ¬ß4b ‚Üí ¬ß5b references corrected throughout RNH code block; 'shows-box row order' ‚Üí 'entry row order' in row-order check label; 'Top 4' ‚Üí 'Minimum 5' in walk-distance check label (per 2026-05-23 rule change that raised minimum to 5)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "ü´ï Restaurants Near Hotel tram exemption: missing-üöï FAIL now skipped when üöé tram is present in entry body (¬ß5b tram alternative: üö∂ X min ‚Üí üöé [N] ‚Üí üö∂ T min; validator previously always failed on missing üöï even when a valid tram route was provided)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "ü´ï Restaurants Near Hotel ‚Äî five new checks added: (A) annotation leakage ([UPDATE]/üî¥/[TBD] etc. in heading or entry body hard-fail); (B) no <p> tags inside entry body (section uses row divs, not paragraphs); (C) duplicate restaurant names within section (copy-paste error); (D) inverse negative-finding (entries present ‚Üí 'No restaurants within 25 min walk' must NOT appear); (E) no preamble prose before first entry (¬ß5 starts immediately with entries, no intro paragraph). All five match the Cappuccino/Downtown pattern."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Shows dead postal-code code removed: _SHOWS_POSTAL_RE compile + shows_no_postal_code population were dead since 2026-05-19 rule reversal (global postal-code check covers all sections per user: 'shows_no_postal_code we dont need by section this should be global fail')"),
    ("2026-05-25", "Shows O‚ÄìW checks implemented: 9 phantom variables (O=<p> tags in shows-box, P=no intro preamble, Q=desc‚â•10chars, R=desc plain text no links, S=ticket link text non-empty, T=no star in heading, U=motion dot separator, V=walk time integer, W=inverse negative-finding) were declared but never populated or checked ‚Äî all now enforced"),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöå Getting Around dead-code removal: (1) orphan stale comment '# RIDE APPS EMPTY-CASE NEGATIVE FINDING' removed; (2) old single-block empty-case check (regex matching legacy 'üöï Ride apps' heading) retired ‚Äî superseded 2026-05-19 by per-app extras-sub entries; (3) old ride-app link-row check (class=ride-app divs) retired ‚Äî class no longer exists in current guides; active coverage is the PER-APP TRANSIT-BOX LINK-ONLY block (added 2026-05-24). Garbled check label fixed: '‚Äî = ride apps' corrected to '¬ß1 ‚Äî ride apps must be first'."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üèõ Stop Titles ‚Äî .guided modifier hard-fail completed: MOD_CLASSES changed from ('guided', 'self') to ('self',) ‚Äî any .stop-name.guided now fails check (A) as 'missing modifier' (guided retired 2026-05-20, per Stops Structure.html ¬ß2); guided branch in check (C) retired as dead code; check (D) comment updated (Type 3 Alternation retired along with guided); check (A) and (C) labels updated to reflect self-only; mutual-exclusion tombstone comment updated; Coverage item 100 'to-do' note resolved."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Michelin dead postal-code code removed: _mich_postal_re compile + mich_no_postal_code population were dead since 2026-05-19 rule reversal; declaration and entry-loop code cleaned up (same pattern as Downtown Restaurants K / Shows H removals)"),
    ("2026-05-25", "üèì Pickleball audit ‚Äî 4 fixes: (1) stale aliases pb_body/pb_body_sfx/_pb_body_shape removed ‚Äî all references now use _pb_inner directly (no logic change, eliminates confusion); (2) retired redundant global description-length check for Pickleball ‚Äî per-entry shape check already handles ‚â§80 chars with accurate icon positions; global check used a 'first non-empty div' heuristic that could misfire on empty-description entries; (3) removed ~? from walk time regex (r'üö∂\\s*(\\d+)\\s*min') ‚Äî tilde must no longer silently pass; added dedicated no-tilde scan over each entry's text body (same pattern as WC-X6, hardcoded per Motion Rule); (4) ¬ß 3 address format: added per-entry checks for postal code (US ZIP 5-digit) and country names in the üìç row ‚Äî both are explicitly banned by Pickleball - Extra Section.html ¬ß3; _PB_COUNTRY_RE pre-compiled before entry loop."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üìí Stop Descriptions audit (Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß 2 Pos 1) ‚Äî 2 fixes: (1) dead check removed: _shows_gap_hits was always [] (rule retired 2026-05-15 ‚Äî no üìí required before shows-box); declaration + check() call both removed, comment retained as tombstone; (2) annotation leakage check added: [UPDATE]/[CHECK]/üî¥/[TBD] etc. in üìí description text now hard-fail ‚Äî scoped to stop-block bodies (reuses _stop_block_bodies_desc); same pattern as stop-name annotation leakage, WC-ANNOT, and CAP-ANNOT. Coverage confirmed complete: length ‚â§320, no links, required on every stop-block, no merged üìíüìñ, no üìí inside tour-box, üìñ order (before/immediately-after) all previously enforced."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî entry format updated: station heading (extras-sub) must now start with üöÜ (local/regional) or üöÑ (high-speed); hard-fail when icon prefix is absent. Route-row ban exempted for extras-sub (was incorrectly catching the icon prefix). CORE RULES ¬ß 3 split into ¬ß 3a Local & Regional Stations (üöÜ [Station Name]) and ¬ß 3b High-Speed Stations (üöÑ [Station Name]). Checksum updated."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî stop-block checks: (1) every .stop-block must contain at least one üèõÔ∏è opening-hours row (hard fail); (2) no .stop-block may have a üö∂ walk time > 40 min (hard fail). Both scoped to main itinerary stop-blocks only, not extra sections."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî reverted inline-icon-in-body check: the 2026-05-25 check requiring both üöÜ and üöÑ in the entry body was wrong. Per ¬ß 3a/¬ß3b, the icon belongs on the heading (extras-sub) only; description row is plain [Lines] ‚Üí [Key Destinations]. Check removed; heading-icon enforcement (already present) is sufficient."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üö¶ Motion Rule ¬ß1 time-format enforcement ‚Äî üö∂/üöï times ‚â•60 min must use Xh Ymin (or Xh when Y=0); 'N min' with N‚â•60 now hard-fails with a suggested correction. _unit_re updated to strip Xh Ymin in leftover-prose check. Motion Rule.html ¬ß1 updated with explicit format rule."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üö¶ Motion / Transit Banners audit (Motion Rule.html) ‚Äî 1 fix: dead guided-stop üöê block removed (lines 4842‚Äì4910, ~70 lines). The .guided CSS class was retired 2026-05-20; _guided_sn_re always returned False on all current guides; _guided_next_violations was always []; check() passed vacuously every run. Tombstone comment added. Coverage verified complete against all three rule sections: ¬ß1 stops pattern (üö∂/üöï N min, tram/metro inline) ‚Äî _validate_motion_row; ¬ß2 extra sections with motion (Cappuccino, RNH, Stations, Pickleball, Shows) and without (Downtown, Local Tastes, Michelin, Heads Up) ‚Äî each has dedicated row-type enforcement; ¬ß3 day wrapper (opener, between-stops, closer, train variants, üöâ ARRIVE banner) ‚Äî covered by opener/closer/bookend/train-header/arrive-first checks. No gaps found."),
    ("2026-05-25", "Trip Overview extras pill label text hard-fail added: every .overview-extra-link visible label must exactly match the canonical name defined in Trip Overview.html ¬ß 3 (owner-defined decisions, not formatting). _OVERVIEW_PILL_CANONICAL_LABELS dict maps href anchor ‚Üí required label text. Canonical labels: weekly-closures‚Üí'üóìÔ∏è Weekly Closures', tours‚Üí'üìÖ Tours', cappuccino‚Üí'‚òï Cappuccino', restaurants‚Üí'ü´ï Restaurants Near Hotel', downtown‚Üí'üçΩÔ∏è Downtown Restaurants', local-tastes‚Üí'üçÆ Local Tastes', food-delivery‚Üí'üöó Food Delivery', shows‚Üí'üé≠ Shows', getting-around‚Üí'üöå Getting Around', stations-near-hotel‚Üí'üöÜ Stations Near Hotel', day-trips‚Üí'‚õ≤Ô∏è Day Trips by Train', pickleball‚Üí'üèì Pickleball', michelin‚Üí'‚≠ê Michelin Restaurants', heads-up‚Üí'‚ùó Heads Up'. All 16 guides updated to match."),
    ("2026-05-25", "üö¶ Motion Rule ‚Äî two consecutive motion rows hard-fail: any two adjacent <div> rows both starting with üö∂ or üöï inside the same box (shows-box, entry-body, station-box) are a hard fail. üö∂ and üöï must share a single row ('üö∂ N min ¬∑ üöï M min'); splitting them is format drift. Scoped to extras boxes only (stop-blocks enforce via _validate_motion_row already)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Food review link format check ‚Äî outer regex blind-spot fixed: _food_review_re previously matched only class='review-link' anchors whose text already contained ‚≠ê AND 'reviews'; anchors with wrong text (‚òÖ star, no star, no 'reviews') were silently invisible and passed. Outer regex changed from ([^<]*‚≠ê[^<]*reviews[^<]*) to ([^<]+) ‚Äî ALL class='review-link' anchors are now validated against the N.N‚≠ê ¬∑ N+ reviews format. Applies to Cappuccino / Restaurants Near Hotel / Downtown (all 3 food sections)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Food review link ‚Äî must have class='review-link' check added: any <a> in .extras-sub whose text matches the rating pattern (N.N‚≠ê ¬∑ N+ reviews) must carry class='review-link'. Without it, CSS rule '.extras-sub a { color: inherit; font-weight: inherit }' renders the link dark+bold (heading color) instead of blue (#2867c4) + normal weight. New hard-fail covers all 3 food sections (Cappuccino / RNH / Downtown)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Food review link ‚Äî no <strong> inside review-link check added: a <strong> tag inside class='review-link' overrides the CSS font-weight:normal rule, making the rating text bold. New hard-fail catches any <strong> inside any class='review-link' anchor."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üéü ticket-box star rating regex tightened: _star_rating_re changed from \\d+\\.?\\d*\\s*‚≠ê (decimal optional, space before star allowed) to \\d+\\.\\d‚≠ê (decimal required, no space). Old pattern accepted '4‚≠ê' (integer, no decimal) and '4.5 ‚≠ê' (space before star) ‚Äî both violate the tight N.N‚≠ê format rule (locked 2026-05-20). Ticket entries must use exactly N.N‚≠ê with one decimal place."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî transport icons banned from description row: üöÜ and üöÑ must appear only on the extras-sub heading, never inside the station-box description row. Per ¬ß 3a/¬ß3b, description row is plain [Lines] ‚Üí [Key Destinations] ‚Äî no transport icons. New hard-fail scans the first content row of each station entry and fails when üöÜ or üöÑ is found there (e.g. 'Alfa Pendular üöÑ connection hub' is a fail)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üö∑ Skip List cross-check ‚Äî venues named in the skip list must not also appear as tour entries in the Tours section. Skip = intentionally excluded; shipping the same venue as a tour contradicts the editorial decision. Hard-fail: extracts significant keywords (‚â•5 chars, not generic travel words) from each skip-list item and checks if any keyword appears in a Tours extras-sub heading."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üí° Claude Inspiration T1b ‚Äî Skip List before CI hard-fail added: when both claude-inspiration and skip-list are present, skip-list must appear AFTER claude-inspiration (correct order: claude-inspiration ‚Üí skip-list). Prior T1 check only enforced that non-skip-list sections don't follow CI; it never checked skip-list appearing before CI ‚Äî silent gap fixed."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üöÜ Train Stations Near Hotel ‚Äî non-rail transport words banned from description row: bus ¬∑ car ¬∑ plane ¬∑ airplane ¬∑ aircraft ¬∑ flight ¬∑ ferry ¬∑ coach ¬∑ taxi ¬∑ shuttle must not appear in the station-box description row. Section is rail-only; any of these words in a description row indicates drift into other transport modes. Hard-fail on whole-word match (case-insensitive)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üö¢ Ferry added as motion icon (position 8e): inline transit row format 'üö¢ N min ‚Üí [Destination]' and Getting Around section entry (‚â§80 chars). Validator updated: üö¢ added to _first_motion ARRIVE-banner search, row trigger for _validate_motion_row, and _MOTION_LEAD_RE consecutive-motion check. Rules updated: Motion Rule.html ¬ß1, Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß2 row 8e + ¬ß3 Getting Around, Emoji Library moved from available to reserved."),
    ("2026-05-26", "‚õ≤Ô∏è Day Trips renamed to Day Trips by Train everywhere: CORE RULES file, section title, anchor id (day-trips-by-train), validator canonical references, all 16 guides, Coverage, Dependency Map. day-trips is now the legacy backward-compat id. Non-train transport language check expanded from headings-only to full section content (drive/car/taxi/bus/ride/shuttle/etc.)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "DECISION LOCKS block added to validator: positive assertions that major decisions cannot drift back. Locks: (1) walk cap >44 min hard fail with no sentinel override; (2) Day Trips by Train ‚Äî title must say 'by Train', anchor must be day-trips-by-train, build_state.md must reference renamed file; (3) üé´ format must always be 'üé´ book at: <link>' globally ‚Äî no bare üé´ without prefix. Complements existing retired-pattern drift sentinels (which ban old patterns) with required-pattern locks (which assert current standards). CORE RULES files fixed: Trip Overview anchor updated to #day-trips-by-train; Icon Order and Format üé´ sub-row label updated to 'Day Trips by Train booking'. Build_state.md in all 16 guides updated from Day Trips - Extra Section.html ‚Üí Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html. Pasadena negative finding rewritten (removed 'car' ‚Äî banned word). Sydney orphaned transit divs removed."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üöä LEAVE banner ‚Äî .leave-first class introduced (2026-05-26): replaces the .next div that was shadowing üöÜ for station-bound return motion; 7 guides updated (Lisbon, Turin, London, Paris√ó3, Sydney); guide_v2.css updated (.leave-first = same blue banner as .arrive-first). Validator: leave-first added to all banner regex patterns and class lists; TRAIN-DAY LEAVE warn check (missing .leave-first per train-day block); üöä LEAVE format check (hard-fail if .leave-first does not start with 'üöä LEAVE {city}:'); drift sentinel (hard-fail if .next div heads to a train station ‚Äî must be .leave-first)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "üöä‚Üíüöù metro icon reassignment + üöä LEAVE banner added: metro icon changed from üöä to üöù in Getting Around ¬ß3, Motion Rule ¬ß1, Icon Order ¬ß2 row 8d; üöä LEAVE {station} banner added to Motion Rule ¬ß3b and Icon Order ¬ß4 row 5 as departure counterpart to üöâ ARRIVE. Validator: üöä‚Üíüöù in _GA_ALLOWED_ICONS, _GA_ICONS_RE, metro section detection, all Metro A/B/C check labels; üöù added to _logistic_lead and arrive-strip motion search. Drift sentinel: old üöä-as-metro section heading hard-fails. CORE RULES updated: Getting Around - Extra Section.html ¬ß3, Motion Rule.html ¬ß1 + ¬ß3b, Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß2 8d + ¬ß4 rows 4‚Äì5."),
    ("2026-05-26", "‚õ≤Ô∏è Day Trips by Train ‚Äî Omio check added: every üé´ booking row in a Day Trips transit-box must include an omio.com link (hard fail). Per Day Trips by Train - Extra Section.html ¬ß2 entry format: 'üé´ book at: [Train Ticket Operator] or [Omio]'. Coverage: Day Trips 15 ‚Üí 16 items."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Brain-wide rename ‚Äî What Goes Into a Guide.html + Types of Days and Stops.html consolidated into Stops Structure.html: BUILD_STATE_PHASE_1 updated (What Goes Into a Guide.html ‚Üí Stops Structure.html); BUILD_STATE_PHASE_2 entry for Types of Days and Stops.html removed; drift-protection section renamed WHAT GOES INTO A GUIDE ‚Üí STOPS STRUCTURE, path updated to Stops Structure.html, all anchor labels updated from ¬ß4/¬ß5 ‚Üí ¬ß1; all remaining inline string refs to both removed filenames replaced with Stops Structure.html throughout."),
    ("2026-05-26", "Train icon system corrected across CORE RULES + validator: üöä = regional train ROUTE HEADER (.train-header div); üöÑ = high-speed train ROUTE HEADER; üöâ = ARRIVE banner (.arrive-first); üöÜ = section icon only (Stations Near Hotel + Trip Overview Train Day label ‚Äî never in .train-header). CORE RULES fixed: Icon Order and Format ¬ß4, Motion Rule ¬ß3b (train day opener/headers), Day Structure ¬ß7, Stops Structure train examples. Validator: _TRAIN_HEADER_LEAD/_FORMAT regexes [üöÜüöÑ]‚Üí[üöäüöÑ]; check labels updated; .leave-first concept DELETED (introduced same day, removed same day ‚Äî was wrong pattern); stale .leave-first hard-fail added; TRAIN-DAY LEAVE check block replaced with stale-div hard-fail; üöä removed from arrive-strip motion search; üöä removed from _logistic_lead (train route headers never appear in extras sections)."),
    ("2026-05-26", "HOTEL NAME CHECK removed: the manual-confirm warn that surfaced .title-hotel names for human verification was removed at Dani's request ‚Äî it added no automated value and produced noise on every run."),
    ("2026-05-29", "LINK_COLOR_ALLOWLIST expanded ‚Äî 18 guide-toolbar theme link-color entries added (9 themes √ó 2 selectors each: .guide-toolbar.theme-{name} .toolbar-nav a and .toolbar-essentials a; colours: purple #7030a0, teal #1c8a99, coral #c85a54, pink #d4336c, sage #6b9080, amber #d97706, indigo #4338ca, green #059669, yellow #eab308). Triggered by new theme CSS blocks added to guide_v2.css on 2026-05-29 during √Ölesund v1 ship gate."),
    ("2026-05-30", 'Missing <!-- low-count: [reason] --> comment is now a hard FAIL (was warn/nudge). Affects: Cappuccino, Restaurants Near Hotel, Downtown Restaurants, Tours. The comment is the required acknowledgment to ship below the minimum ‚Äî without it the guide cannot ship. Guides with the comment still only warn on the count itself.'),
    ("2026-05-30", '"‚Üí hotel" global ban added ‚Äî hard fail when "‚Üí hotel" appears anywhere outside .next / .arrive-first / .leave-first banner divs (the only legitimate locations). Catches template leakage in tour entries, stop descriptions, or any other content. Per Motion Rule ‚Äî end-of-day closer and train arrival only.'),
    ("2026-05-30", '"‚Üí time from hotel" global template-leakage check added ‚Äî guide-wide hard fail (not just Tours section) when the literal phrase "time from hotel" appears anywhere in shipped HTML. Covers all sections: Tours, day blocks, stops. Scans after stripping <script>/<style>/comments. Per Tours - Extra Section.html ¬ß 4.'),
    ("2026-05-29", "TOOLBAR section added (TB-1 through TB-8): TB-1 toolbar-mount div present; TB-2 data-depth='2' for Guides pages; TB-3 data-maxwidth='940' for guides; TB-4 toolbar.js script tag present with correct ../../toolbar.js path; TB-5 toolbar-mount appears before .title-page (toolbar is first item inside .container ‚Äî all guides place it there, not outside the container); TB-6 script tag immediately follows mount div (closing </div> + whitespace only between); TB-7/TB-8 data-prev/data-next (when present) are relative intra-Guides paths (../CityName/file.html), never external URLs ‚Äî prev/next stay inside Guides/. 'Nothing before .title-page' check updated to exempt toolbar mount + script. ‚Üë back-to-top button (.tb-top) is JS-generated at runtime ‚Äî not in source HTML, not validated. Source: Brain/Reference/Toolbar.html."),
    ("2026-05-29", "TB-9 added ‚Äî footer sharing link check: every shipped guide must include a centered div containing dbellinello.github.io/travel_guides/Guides/{City}/{file}.html as the last element before </body>. Cosmetic public URL for sharing. Rule added to Toolbar.html ¬ß6; Rules for Claude.html ¬ß4 publishing section updated to reference it."),
    ("2026-05-29", "TB-7/TB-8 updated ‚Äî data-prev/data-next now accept both ../ (guide‚Üíguide or guide‚Üíindex) and ./ (index‚Üíguide) relative paths. Guides-Index.html added to the guide cycle as a full stop between Marrakech and Bend."),
    ("2026-05-30", "Tram template: accept 'Lines' as well as 'Line(s)' ‚Äî global parentheses ban conflicts with original template literal; both forms now pass."),
    ("2026-05-31", "TB-10 added ‚Äî carousel chain check: every depth-2 guide page must have both data-prev and data-next on its toolbar-mount (being in the carousel is mandatory, not optional); chain must also be bidirectionally consistent (prev.data-next and next.data-prev must both resolve back to this guide). Catches the Alaska failure mode: guide listed in guides_index but unreachable via ‚Üê/‚Üí because toolbar-mount had no prev/next. urllib.parse.unquote added to imports for %20-encoded paths."),
    ("2026-05-30", "TB-9 rewritten ‚Äî the footer sharing link is now INJECTED by toolbar.js (one definition for every page) instead of a per-file inline div. Each page links to its own live URL (location-based), so it is repo-rename-proof. TB-9 now passes when a guide loads toolbar.js AND has no stale inline footer div; it fails on a leftover hardcoded github.io footer. Triggered by the GitHub repo rename travel_guides ‚Üí Travel and footer centralization. Toolbar.html ¬ß5 rewritten to match."),
    ("2026-06-06", "TOOLBAR HOME MOVED INSIDE Guides/ ‚Äî toolbar.js and footnote.js now live at Guides/toolbar.js and Guides/footnote.js, PERMANENTLY. They must never be moved back to Travel root. TB-4 updated: guide pages load <script src=\"../toolbar.js\"> (1 level up to Guides/), not ../../. toolbar.js loads footnote.js from {base}Guides/footnote.js. Non-guide pages: depth-1 pages use ../Guides/toolbar.js, depth-2 pages outside Guides/ use ../../Guides/toolbar.js, Guides-Index.html uses toolbar.js. brain_check.py fails if either script is missing from Guides/ or a stray copy reappears at Travel root. Source: Brain/Reference/Toolbar.html ¬ß1."),
    ("2026-05-30", "CORE RULES integrity guard hardened ‚Äî the checksum loop now re-reads a file (2 retries, 0.25s apart) before recording a mismatch. The CORE RULES files stream from Google Drive File Stream; a cold read of a not-yet-hydrated file returned partial bytes and produced a spurious hash mismatch, which failed the ship-gate at random on the first run of a session (observed: Oslo 671/2-fail on cold run, 673/0 on every warm run). A real unauthorized edit never self-heals, so the retry only clears hydration flakes. Found in the 2026-05-30 validator audit."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Train Day destination ‚âÝ guide city check added ‚Äî hard fail when a 'Day N ‚Äî Train Day ‚Äî {City}' header lists the guide's own city as the destination. Stops Structure.html ¬ß3c defines Train Day as a round-trip to ANOTHER city; a self-referential Train Day is nonsensical."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Day Trips destination conflict check added ‚Äî hard fail when a Day Trips entry lists (A) the guide's own city or (B) a city already covered in the itinerary. Suggesting a city you are already visiting is redundant regardless of how it is structured. City comparison is case-insensitive; travel-time suffix stripped before compare."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Link-color allowlist updated for 2026-05-31 CSS design token changes: CANONICAL_LINK_BLUE #2867c4 ‚Üí #8a6c1a (global link color changed to gold in guide_v2.css); toolbar-nav/essentials expected color #3d5f80 ‚Üí #6b4422 (--c-title-bg warm chestnut); #tours .extras-sub a and .title-page .title-address a added to allowlist."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Day Trips duplicate-destination check label updated ‚Äî removed incorrect framing 'Train Day is a full itinerary day, not an optional excursion' (Train Days and Day Trips have the same time requirements; the only reason to exclude is redundancy with the planned itinerary)."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Getting Around icon allowlist expanded: üö¢ (Ferry) added to _GA_ALLOWED_ICONS alongside üöï üöé üöù. Getting Around - Extra Section.html ¬ß4 defines ferry as a valid subsection when a ferry route is relevant to in-city travel. üö¢ is not added to the GA drift check because it is also a legitimate motion banner icon used elsewhere in guides."),
    ("2026-05-31", "idx-coverage-self + idx-coverage-all: FAIL if this guide or any guide folder is absent from Guides-Index.html ‚Äî unlisted guide is invisible to carousel and navigation"),
    ("2026-05-31", "carousel-alpha: FAIL if carousel chain (data-guide-next in Guides-Index.html) is not in pure global A\u2192Z order by city name (diacritics normalized). Carousel ignores region grouping used by the index."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Guides-Index.html alphabetical order check added ‚Äî within each .overview-section (region), guides must be in alphabetical order by city name (case-insensitive, diacritics normalized: √Ölesund ‚Üí Alesund, Montr√©al ‚Üí Montreal). One violation reported per out-of-order region. Rule added to Navigation.html ¬ß4."),
    ("2026-06-01", ".title-hotel banned suffix check added: hard-fail when .title-hotel text ends with a generic accommodation word (Home, House, Apartment, Airbnb, Condo, Villa, Cottage, Cabin, Rental Home). Property name only ‚Äî accommodation type is implicit. Bend guide fixed: 'Sunriver Rental Home' ‚Üí 'Sunriver Rental'. No other guides affected."),
    ("2026-06-01", "Hotel banner formatting enforcement added: (1) .title-address must not contain <strong>/<b> or inline font-weight:bold ‚Äî address is plain weight, subordinate to hotel name; (2) .title-hotel must not have an inline style stripping its bold (font-weight:normal/400/etc.) ‚Äî hotel name is the primary label and must remain bold. Both checks enforce the guide-style.css hierarchy: city (large bold) > hotel name (medium bold) > address (small plain). Per Hotel Banner.html ¬ß1."),
    ("2026-06-01", "Link-color allowlist restored: CANONICAL_LINK_BLUE #8a6c1a ‚Üí #2867c4 (guide-style.css restored --c-link to blue on 2026-06-01; validator not updated at the time ‚Äî fixed now). #tours .extras-sub a allowlist entry updated to match (#8a6c1a ‚Üí #2867c4). .index-banner-sub a remains #8a6c1a (--c-purple unchanged). Toolbar colors (#6b4422) unchanged."),
    ("2026-06-01", "Claude Inspiration calibration anchor needles updated: theme-purple/theme-amber/theme-teal removed (spec ¬ß 2 rewritten to 'No fixed palette ‚Äî choose freely'); replaced with 'No fixed palette' and 'theme-{color}' anchors that exist in the updated spec."),
    ("2026-05-31", "Wikimedia hotlink sentinel exemption removed ‚Äî the `<!-- hotlink: CDN download blocked in Cowork sandbox -->` comment no longer authorises a hotlink src. commons_photo.py --download fetches the original file and resizes with PIL, bypassing the CDN thumbnail HTTP 400. ALL upload.wikimedia.org img src values now hard-fail regardless of any sentinel comment. Use `python3 Brain/scripts/commons_photo.py --download Guides/{City}/_build/assets/800px-Foo.jpg \"File:Foo.jpg\"` to convert existing hotlinks."),
    ("2026-06-05", "Day-opener banner casing changed from the all-caps banner form to `üè® From Hotel:` (titlecase) ‚Äî approved convention change. canonical_re flipped FROM\\s+HOTEL ‚Üí From\\s+Hotel (case-sensitive); IGNORECASE opener-presence / exactly-once / time-strip matchers unaffected. All all-caps From Hotel literals across CORE RULES (Day Structure, Motion Rule, Icon Order, Stops Structure) and Brain/Reference (Validator Index, Ship Checklist, Rule Dependencies, Emoji Library, Cleanliness Checks, Separation Map, Guide Style.css) updated to From Hotel. Two outlier guides (Amsterdam, Barcelona) migrated to titlecase; other 35 already titlecase."),
    ("2026-06-05", "TILDE BAN CONSOLIDATED to a single global check with ONE carve-out (‚è∞ Avg Time Spent). Drift fixed: Icon Order and Format.html showed `‚è≥ ~45 min` ‚Äî wrong; ‚è≥ Duration is exact (`‚è≥ 45 min`), the tilde belongs to ‚è∞ only. The former per-section tilde scans (banner body, Weekly Closures WC-X6, Local Tastes, Shows üóí, Pickleball, Heads Up note/heading) were removed ‚Äî all now covered by the one GLOBAL TILDE BAN, broadened from `~\\d` to any `~` not immediately preceded by ‚è∞. Leftover `~?` tolerances stripped from üö∂/üöï motion-parse regexes and cappuccino negative-finding sentinels. CORE RULES updated: Icon Order (‚è≥ examples + Tilde rule note), Rules for Claude.html ¬ß6. CLAUDE.md, Validator Index, Rule Dependencies updated to match."),
    ("2026-06-05", "TERMINOLOGY CLEANUP (Dani): the word 'gotcha' is removed everywhere ‚Äî the section is 'Heads Up' and its detail field is '[Note]'. All validator labels/comments/vars renamed gotcha‚Üínote / 'Cities Gotchas'‚Üí'Heads Up'. CORE RULES (Heads Up Extra Section, Icon Order) field renamed [Gotcha]‚Üí[Note]; Rules for Claude PDF line 'all gotchas'‚Üí'all edge cases'. Swept across Reference docs, mds, CLAUDE.md, guide comments, and CSS comments."),
    ("2026-06-05", "DECISION LOCKS extended (so renames cannot drift back): (5) literal 'Trip at a Glance' anywhere in a guide hard-fails ‚Äî the section is 'Trip Overview'; (6) 'Gotcha(s)' wording hard-fails ‚Äî the section is 'Heads Up'. From-Hotel casing already locked by the case-sensitive `üè® From Hotel:` titlecase check. All all-caps 'FROM HOTEL' literals removed from active rules/refs (historical decision/audit entries reworded to 'uppercase ‚Üí titlecase')."),
    ("2026-06-05", "FINAL GATE relocated to the very END of validation (Dani): the two membership checks ‚Äî guide listed in Guides-Index.html AND city pinned in a continent map ‚Äî now run last, as the final gate, instead of mid-run. A guide fails for a missing index entry / map pin only at the end. Self-contained block (recomputes paths); the mid-validation copies were removed (CAROUSEL keeps its own _idx_html2)."),
    ("2026-06-05", "HEADS UP false-positive fixed: trip-city‚ÜîHeads Up entry matching was a bare substring scan, which fired 'nice' inside 'venice' ‚Äî Venice wrongly required a Heads Up section it has no entry for. Switched to a word-boundary regex match (\\b‚Ä¶\\b); still matches compound titles like 'PASADENA & GREATER LA' ‚Üí 'Pasadena'."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Underline ban re-homed to Links.html ¬ß 8 (Dani-approved): the rule lost its CORE RULES home when Icon Order ¬ß 6 was dropped in a rewrite. New ¬ß 8 added to Links.html; check label + comment now cite Links.html ¬ß 8. Check logic unchanged."),
    ("2026-06-06", "Label fix only ‚Äî inline-underline check cited Icon Order and Format.html ¬ß 6, a section that no longer exists (file now has ¬ß¬ß 1‚Äì4). Label now cites the guide-style.css global a/a:visited rule. Check logic unchanged."),
